Inside the coffin was a black hen with a rosary tied around its neck. [Harold Odhiambo, Standard]  Residents of Kogony village in Kisumu were shocked after they found a coffin with 'witchcraft paraphernalia' dumped at a home.  Inside the coffin was a black hen with a rosary tied around its neck, a snail and an item wrapped up in a polythene bag.  Villagers taking photos of the 'witchcraft paraphernalia'. [Harold Odhiambo, Standard] Help us serve you better by completing our quick survey. Villagers thronged the home and milled around the coffin to find out what it contained.  Double blow to family as man’s body missing  Locals bury goat's blood after body of granny is exhumed  How fear of the spirits of the dead led to mix up of bodies in morgue  Njuri Ncheke elders arrest 'witchcraft' suspect, find dead bats, locks of human hair in house It took several hours before police officers, who visited the scene, opened it.   The coffin was found by a herder. [Harold Odhiambo, Standard]  Sylvester Okore, who found the coffin next to his gate, said his herdsman woke him up to inform him about the coffin.  "I was shocked, and after confirming, I immediately informed area assistant chief who alerted police at Riat police post,” he said.  The paraphernalia were set ablaze. [Harold Odhiambo, Standard]  He suspects a close relative could be behind the dumping of the coffin.    Another resident, who sought anonymity, alleged that the incident could be related to a land dispute between two brothers.   Curse of Grey hair in Kilifi County  Drama as suspected thief returns to scene of crime with stolen TV set stuck on his head  Maajabu ya Uganga: Televisheni yakwama kichwani mwa mshukiwa wa wizi Teso By Kevine Omollo  | 22 hours ago By Eric Abuga and Harold Odhiambo | 1 day ago By Kevine Omollo  | 2 days ago By James Omoro | 2 days ago